{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 13:38:40.768054", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Thanks — I submitted the solution.\n\nSummary of submitted solution:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- Faulty devices: host_1_1_1_1, host_1_1_1_2, host_2_1_2_1, server_access_router, router_dist_1_1\n- Root cause(s) selected: host_missing_ip, http_acl_block\n\nNotes:\n- host_missing_ip corresponds to the observed hosts having eth0 UP but no IPv4 address (DHCP/host-side issue).\n- http_acl_block was chosen to represent missing/misapplied segmentation/ACL that allows hosts to reach backend web servers contrary to design.\n\nIf you want, I can now run the recommended diagnostic checks (DHCP lease/log checks, relay config, access switch port status, host DHCP client logs, and ACL/filter validation) to further narrow the issues and produce remediations. Which of those would you like me to perform?", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2807, "output_tokens": 197, "total_tokens": 3004, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2688}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
